<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

    <head>
        <title>Privacy Policy | Midwest Alliance for Applied Genomic Epidemiology</title>
        <%- include('../head') %>
    </head>

    <body class="claro patric <% if (request.isAuthenticated && request.isAuthenticated()) { %>Authenticated<% } %>">
        <div id="ApplicationContainer" data-dojo-type="dijit/layout/BorderContainer" class="layoutContainer"
            data-dojo-props="id:'ApplicationContainer',gutters:false,liveSplitters:false">
            <%- include('../navbar') %>
            <div data-dojo-type="dijit/layout/ContentPane" data-dojo-props="region:'center'"
                style="padding:0px;border:0px solid #ddd;background:inherit;">
                <div id="bv-brc-page">
                    <div id="bv-brc-page-container" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="page-content" style="width:80%; margin: 0 auto; text-align:left;">
                            <style>
                                h1 {
                                    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
                                    font-weight: 600;
                                    margin: 0;
                                    padding: 0;
                                }

                                p {
                                    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
                                    font-weight: 400;
                                    font-size: 16px;
                                    line-height: 1.5;
                                }
                            </style>
                            <div class="max-w-[75%] mx-auto">

                                <h1 id="privacy-policy" class="text-2xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-6">Privacy
                                    Policy</h1>
                                <p>The Midwest Alliance for Applied Genomic Epidemiology (MAAGE) is provided as a public
                                    resource to support genomic surveillance and epidemiological research. 
                                    This Privacy Policy describes the ways MAAGE collects, stores, uses, discloses and protects the personal information about users
                                    and how they use MAAGE. MAAGE never collects information for commercial marketing or
                                    any purpose unrelated to MAAGE functions.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">Information MAAGE collects</h2>
                                <p>Many functions of MAAGE, such as data browsing, may be used without a MAAGE User
                                    Account. MAAGE uses Google Analytics to accumulate this type of web traffic
                                    information in order to measure and report overall usage of the website portion of
                                    the resource. More information can be found in <a
                                        class="cursor-pointer hover:underline"
                                        href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245?hl=en"
                                        target="_blank">Google Analytics data practices</a>.</p>
                                <br>
                                <p>If you choose to have a MAAGE User Account, you are asked to provide your name and an
                                    email address so that we may contact you if needed, for instance, if there is a
                                    problem with your account. This information is stored in your private personal
                                    profile. You are also required to provide a Username, which is used for logging in
                                    and appears along with data that you choose to share. MAAGE Usernames are not
                                    treated as personal information and it is recommended that you not include personal
                                    information in your Username.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">User-provided personal information and data</h2>
                                <p>You may at your discretion also provide in your personal profile further biographical
                                    information including your organization, organisms of interest, and other research
                                    interests. This information may be used in aggregate to understand the MAAGE
                                    userbase in order to improve the resource.</p>
                                <br>
                                <p>MAAGE does not track information in your personal research data. Access to this
                                    information is strictly under your control to share or make public. If you are
                                    having problems with your data in the private workspace or in using MAAGE services
                                    and you request our help, we may access your workspace and data files to
                                    troubleshoot and help resolve the problem for you</p>
                                <br>
                                <p>Once you share data or workspaces with others MAAGE users or make it public, be aware
                                    that other users will be able to access the data. You can turn off the sharing at a
                                    later time if you desire.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">User behavioral profile</h2>
                                <p>When you use MAAGE services that require login (such as Genome Annotation), usage
                                    information is automatically recorded by your Username including what services you
                                    used, time of submission, service input parameters, and input/output file locations.
                                </p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">How information collected by MAAGE is used</h2>
                                <p>Private personal information such as email address is only accessible to MAAGE staff
                                    and will only be used individually in the event we need to contact you. If you
                                    choose to provide that information to MAAGE independently (for example when emailing
                                    to request help), again it will only be used by MAAGE staff for the purpose of
                                    responding. MAAGE will produce project reports that include aggregate information
                                    such as the number of help requests, statistics on the topics of requests and
                                    resolutions. Additionally, the ways users interact with the system are analyzed when
                                    errors occur and in aggregate for analysis of MAAGE operation and improvement.</p>
                                <br>
                                <p>Aggregated usage information based on user behavior is used by MAAGE to produce
                                    overall statistics such as to show users which services are most popular. Usage
                                    information is also used by MAAGE for internal purposes such as to manage and
                                    improve capabilities and services, the website and related features and content, and
                                    to enable users to easily and productively navigate the website and utilize MAAGE
                                    capabilities for research benefit.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">Information MAAGE discloses</h2>
                                <p>MAAGE is committed to maintaining the confidentiality, integrity and security of
                                    users’ personal private information and data. Usage information is used in aggregate
                                    for reporting to the funding agencies for the purpose of assessing the performance of the overall project. 
                                    Aggregate usage information may also be used in presentations and reported publicly through the
                                    Performance and Usage Metrics, available from the About MAAGE page on the MAAGE
                                    website. No individually identifiable information is reported or disclosed.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">Relationship to BV-BRC</h2>
                                <p>MAAGE shares a the database, analysis services, website, and user authentication infrastructure that has been
                                    developed by the Bacterial and Viral Bioinformatics Resource Center Project (<a
                                        class="cursor-pointer hover:underline"
                                        href="https://www.bv-brc.org/about" target="_blank">BV-BRC</a>). BV-BRC shares
                                    the same <a class="cursor-pointer hover:underline"
                                        href="https://www.bv-brc.org/privacy-policy" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>
                                    as MAAGE. Communication and aggregation of usage data, as described above may also
                                    occur in accordance with the BV-BRC privacy policy and be used for reporting
                                    aggregate usage metrics for the BV-BRC sponsor, the National Institute of Allergy
                                    and Infectious Diseases.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">How information MAAGE collects is protected</h2>
                                <p>MAAGE restricts access to nonpublic, personal information to those staff and service
                                    providers involved in administering and servicing user accounts. Physical,
                                    electronic and procedural safeguards are in place that comply with Federal standards
                                    to protect such information.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">Changes to this policy</h2>
                                <p>This MAAGE Privacy Policy may change from time to time. Your rights under this policy
                                    will not be reduced without your explicit consent. Changes will be posted on this
                                    page, and if significant, will be provided more prominently via email or
                                    notification when you sign in.</p>
                                <br>

                                <p>Users may at any time review, update, correct or delete the personal information in
                                    their profiles by signing in to their MAAGE account and using the edit or remove
                                    functions available from their personal profile page.</p>
                                <br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-poppins pt-4 pb-2">Other Information</h2>
                                <p class="cursor-pointer hover:underline"><a href="/about">About MAAGE</a></p>
                                <p class="cursor-pointer hover:underline"><a class="DialogButton"
                                        rel="reportProblem:">Contact Us</a></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
            <%- include('../footer') %>
        </div>
        </div>

        <%- include('../javascript') %>
    </body>

</html>